FuncDef:
The qos buffer overrun alarm enable command enables the device to generate an alarm when the queue buffer exceeds the threshold.
The undo qos buffer overrun alarm enable command disables the device from generating an alarm when the queue buffer exceeds the threshold. The qos buffer overrun alarm enable command enables the device to generate an alarm when the queue buffer exceeds the threshold. The undo qos buffer overrun alarm enable command disables the device from generating an alarm when the queue buffer exceeds the threshold. By default, the device is disabled from generating an alarm when the queue buffer exceeds the threshold.
CLIs: undo qos buffer overrun alarm enable
